---
// Story 2.6 — the vision/manifesto stub route (Decision B: /vision).
//
// No vision/why/manifesto content page exists yet (future content), so the
// header "the vision" link and the pitch-card "Why a markdown web?" link both
// point at this minimal placeholder. It is a NON-collection Astro route (NOT a
// content/*.md file), so it never enters the `pages` collection and never
// appears in the 2.5 vault index listing. Rendered through `Page`, so it
// inherits the theme + the 2.6 header/pitch chrome and carries its own single
// <h1> (the chrome adds none).
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="Why a markdown web?">
  <h1>Why a markdown web?</h1>
  <p>
    The vision for the Markdown Web is coming soon. The full manifesto — why one
    fixed view isn&rsquo;t enough, and what reading your own way looks like —
    will live here.
  </p>
  <p><a href="/">Back to the web</a></p>
</Page>
